to the editor re when a buyer for hospitals has a stake in drugs it buys front page march 26 alarm bells should be ringing in the ears of both legislators and hospital administrators if buying groups have a financial interest in the success of supply companies they award contracts to then product choice can not be objective the collusion between supplier and buyer not only impedes free trade and ultimately inflates hospital supply costs it may also be endangering the safety of patients andrew mcquide md bridgeport conn march 26 2002

